"This section is specifically about the :doc:`Glossary </glossary/index>` "
"section, where we define common terms in Blender and computer graphics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:101
msgid "Define the term before providing any further information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:102
msgid ""
"Avoid using constructs such as \"it is\" or \"xyz is\" before the "
"definition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:103
msgid "Avoid repeating the term immediately or using it in the definition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:104
msgid "Avoid adding terms not found in Blender's interface or the manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:105
msgid ""
"Avoid overly long entries. If an explanation of a complex term is needed,"
" supplement with external links."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/about/contribute/guides/writing_guide.rst:107
msgid ""
"Avoid duplicating documentation; if explaining the term is the primary "
"focus of another section of the manual (e.g. if the term is the name of a"
" tool), either just link to that section, or avoid creating a glossary "
"entry entirely."
msgstr ""

